"cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL". 

The paper discusses representation learning using Variational Autoencoder (VAE) and neural autoregressive models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The paper also focuses on image data, which suggests that it may fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of autoregressive models and generative modeling also suggests that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the control over what the global latent code can learn, which suggests that it may fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of autoregressive models for both prior distribution and decoding distribution also suggests that it may fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses density estimation tasks, which suggests that it may fall under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
